  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_1' aria-label=\" Syed Basheer Ahmed  versus M/s Tinni Laboratories Private Limited & Anr. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('1','2025','2025_8_1487_1492','2025INSC1030'); ><font size='4'> <strong>SYED BASHEER AHMED <span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>M/S TINNI LABORATORIES PRIVATE LIMITED & ANR. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 8 S.C.R. 1487</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 1030</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010006512025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : PRASHANT KUMAR MISHRA, K. VINOD CHANDRAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration A suit for specific performance was decreed by the trial court, which was dismissed by the High Court in appeal, reversing the judgment and decree. Whether the High Court erred in reversing the findings and the judgment and decree passed by the Suit for specific performance &ndash; A suit was filed by the plaintiff, the appellant herein, alleging that an agreement was entered into with the 1st defendant, the 2nd respondent herein, for purchase of two properties which are more fully described as Item No.1 and Item No.2 &ndash; The trial<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 21-08-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 11080/2014</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Rejected</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('1','2025','2025_8_1487_1492','2025INSC1030','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_spl